  "text": "Cariprazine was over sixfold more potent (EC 50 = 1.4 nmol/L) than aripiprazole (EC 50 = 9.2 nmol/ L) in inhibiting isoproterenol-induced cAMP production in HEK-293 cells; however, both compounds displayed similar maximum effect (~75% of efficacy, in comparison with the full D 2 R agonist quinpirole) ( Fig. 1A; Table 1 ). In this assay, haloperidol demonstrated no intrinsic activity and instead behaved as a potent D 2 R antagonist (data not shown; [CITATION_1] .",
